Actor Moses J Moseley has passed away at 31. According to TMZ, Moseley, who was best known for playing one of Michonne's zombies in the hit series "The Walking dead" was found dead in the Hudson Bridge area, Georgia with a gunshot wound. His family filed a missing persons report after they failed to hear from him for several days. They then called his car company and had it tracked which led them to the location where his lifeless body was found. Moseley who doubled as a writer and model, appeared on other hit shows like: Queen of the South, American Soul, Watchmen and The Hunger Games: Catching Fire among others. His manager Tabatha Minchew confirmed the news of his death on Monday (31 January) on her Facebook page. "Moses was a very talented person, with a bright light around him. He'll be missed deeply by his friends, family and fans." Minchew said in the statement. Fans, colleagues and the team at The Walking Dead paid tributes to Moseley all over social media. “With a heavy heart, we at Avery Sisters Entertainment offer our sincerest and deepest condolences to the family and friends of our actor, Moses J. Moseley. We are truly saddened,” the company wrote on its Facebook page. “For those who knew him, he was the kindest, sweetest, most generous person you would ever meet. We will miss you dearly!" part of the company's Facebook post read. The AMC studios through the official Walking Dead twitter account also paid tribute to Moseley on Monday. “Our thoughts and prayers are with our #TWDFamily member Moses J. Moseley,” the network tweeted. The police are currently investigating how the actor's body ended up in the area. And whether his death it was an act of suicide or if foul play was involved.